// zenoh-mem: N-peer mesh router config template (hub-spoke pattern)
//
// Copy this file once per peer and replace the placeholders below. The
// zenohd_home.json5 / zenohd_office.json5 configs are the 2-peer instance of
// the same pattern; use this template when you want 3+ peers without
// hand-rolling each side from scratch.
//
// Topology recommendation: 1 hub + N spokes.
//   - Pick one peer (typically the always-on home machine) as the hub.
//   - The hub `listen`s on every IP that any spoke can reach (LAN, Tailscale,
//     VPN — aggregate them all). Spokes never need to be reachable from each
//     other.
//   - Each spoke `connect`s to the hub ONLY. Zenoh router transit lets two
//     spokes talk through the hub without a direct link, so adding a new
//     spoke does NOT require touching any existing peer's config or
//     restarting them. Verified empirically 2026-05-10 with 3-PC test
//     (see docs/poc-reports/topology-2026-05-10.md).
//
// Placeholders:
//   {SELF_IP} — this peer's LAN IP (the one the hub will accept incoming on,
//               or the IP MCP clients on the same host will dial)
//   {HUB_IP}  — hub peer's IP that THIS peer can reach
//
// Operational notes:
//   - 127.0.0.1 stays in `listen` so MCP clients on the same host connect via
//     loopback. EXCEPTION on WSL2: the loopback is shared with the Windows
//     host (mirrored networking), so 127.0.0.1:7447 may already be bound;
//     drop the loopback line and pick a non-conflicting port (e.g. 7448) for
//     the LAN listen instead. When you do this, **also point local clients
//     at the new endpoint** — `mesh-mem` and the MCP server read
//     `ZENOH_CONNECT` (default `tcp/127.0.0.1:7447`), so:
//       - For shell use, export `ZENOH_CONNECT=tcp/<SELF_IP>:7448` in the
//         shell or your shell rc.
//       - For Claude Code MCP, pass it on registration:
//           `claude mcp add mesh_mem ... -e ZENOH_CONNECT=tcp/<SELF_IP>:7448 ...`
//     See `docs/poc-reports/topology-2026-05-10.md` §A for the empirical
//     context.
//   - When THIS peer is itself the hub, replace `connect.endpoints` with [] —
//     the hub doesn't dial anyone. Spokes dial in.
//   - storage / replication blocks must match across all peers byte-for-byte:
//     mismatched `interval` / `sub_intervals` / `hot` / `warm` will silently
//     prevent digest convergence.
//   - Set `ZENOH_BACKEND_ROCKSDB_ROOT="$HOME/.local/share/mesh-mem"` before
//     starting zenohd, and ensure the parent directory exists.
//   - Open TCP/7447 (or your chosen port) from every spoke to the hub. The
//     reverse direction is not required (Zenoh sessions are bidirectional
//     once the spoke dials in). See README §Multi-host mesh setup.
//   - Replication digest convergence requires per-peer clock skew < 500 ms.
//     Run NTP/chrony on every host. WSL2 hosts in particular often need
//     a manual `step` after Windows hibernation; `systemd-timesyncd`
//     only slews. Source the reference time from the **hub** (the local
//     `date` on the drifting host is the wrong source by definition),
//     then push it to the WSL2 guest:
//       # on the hub
//       HUB_NOW=$(awk -v t="$(date -u +%s.%3N)" 'BEGIN{printf "%.3f", t+1.0}')   # +1s ssh latency bias
//       ssh wsl2 "sudo timedatectl set-ntp false \
//                  && sudo date -u -s @$HUB_NOW \
//                  && sudo timedatectl set-ntp true"
//     Then re-check skew with `ssh wsl2 'date -u +%s.%3N'` against the
//     hub's `date -u +%s.%3N` and adjust the bias if needed. See
//     `docs/poc-reports/topology-2026-05-10.md` §B for the full
//     procedure.

{
  mode: "router",

  // 127.0.0.1 is for local MCP clients; {SELF_IP} is what peers dial.
  listen: {
    endpoints: [
      "tcp/127.0.0.1:7447",
      "tcp/{SELF_IP}:7447",
    ],
  },

  // Spoke peer: dial the hub only. Zenoh router transit handles the rest.
  // (If THIS peer is the hub, set `endpoints: []` instead.)
  connect: {
    endpoints: [
      "tcp/{HUB_IP}:7447",
    ],
  },

  // replication / storage_manager require timestamping at every level.
  timestamping: {
    enabled: { router: true, peer: true, client: true },
  },

  plugins: {
    storage_manager: {
      volumes: {
        rocksdb: {},
      },
      storages: {
        agent_mem: {
          key_expr: "mem/**",
          strip_prefix: "mem",

          // Keep these values identical on every peer. Mismatched digest
          // parameters break convergence without a visible error.
          replication: {
            interval: 10.0,          // seconds (float ok)
            sub_intervals: 5,
            hot: 6,
            warm: 30,
            propagation_delay: 250,  // milliseconds
          },

          volume: {
            id: "rocksdb",
            // Resolved path: ${ZENOH_BACKEND_ROCKSDB_ROOT}/agent_mem
            dir: "agent_mem",
            create_db: true,
          },
        },
      },
    },
  },
}
